    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look poised for high-impact production today, headlined by the elite 70.02 score for **Gunnar Henderson**. Facing Schlittler, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits significantly from a dynamic platoon edge (+14%) and a favorable leadoff spot, making him the premier play on the board. **Josh Lowe** also presents an exceptional opportunity with a 69.30 rating; he draws a favorable matchup against Martin and receives a double boost from both a platoon advantage and a wind-out scenario. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.92) and **Heliot Ramos** (65.49) are locked into the core, with the latter capitalizing on a strong SP_xERA of 4.91 from V\u00e1squez to drive his upside, further supported by beneficial wind conditions.\n\nThe most challenging decision today involved the final utility and outfield slots, specifically weighing **Jackson Merrill** (54.40) against the rest of the bottom half of the lineup. While **Jackson Merrill** holds a respectable score, his matchup against McDonald (3.08 xERA) presents the highest risk of the day, as the elite pitching skill of the opposition acts as a significant drag on his projection. Despite this, he stays in the lineup over bench options due to his high-leverage batting order position. We remain sidelined with **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jordan Westburg** on the IL, while **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Jacob Wilson** are unavailable due to scheduling. The Waves are keeping a close eye on **Drake Baldwin**, whose 44.73 score is suppressed by a tough matchup against Gilbert; while he is barely above the floor, the lack of depth necessitates the start. Keep a weather eye on the wind reports, as the \"wind out\" advantage is providing the necessary cushion for **Nolan Schanuel** and **Miguel Vargas** to remain viable starts in their respective matchups.",
